#cybersecurity #ransomware #EDR The post you're referring to highlights the gap between having sophisticated EDR (Endpoint Detection and Response) tools in place and actually achieving effective cybersecurity posture against modern threats like ransomware. It suggests that many organizations are failing not because their defenses can be easily bypassed, but due to poor implementation, mismanagement of security configurations, user experience issues with these tools, inadequate support from teams, and a general lack of focus on basic hygiene practices.

